ther runner, use the appropriate command.\n\nNotes and next steps\n- If you actually intended the mixed rounding rule (floor for positives, ceiling otherwise), please confirm. That rule would yield 17 for [1.4, 4.2, 0], not 29, so it contradicts your examples.\n- If you want a different memory trade-off or additional diagnostics (e.g., a dry-run function that returns the per-element rounding outcomes), I can add that to the helper function on request.","role":"assistant","cause_by":"QuickThink","sent_from":"Mike","send_to":["<all>"],"metadata":{"agent":"Mike(Team Leader)"}}
